11 (i) one representative of the Job Opportunities Task Force;
12 (ii) one representative of the Maryland Chiefs of Police Association
13 and the Maryland Sheriffs’ Association;
14 (iii) one representative of a large local detention center;
15 (iv) one representative of a small local detention center;
16 (v) one representative of a county pretrial release program that does
17 not charge fees to participants;
18 (vi) one representative of a county pretrial release program that does
19 charge fees to participants; and
20 (vii) one representative of private home detention monitoring
21 agencies.
22 (c) The President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House shall select two
23 cochairs from among the members of the Workgroup.
24 (d) The Department of Public Safety and Correctional Services shall provide staff
25 for the Workgroup.
26 (e) A member of the Workgroup:
27 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Workgroup; but
28 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
29 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.

