1 (f) A member of the Workgroup serves at the pleasure of the person who
2 appointed the member.
3 (g) At the first meeting of the Workgroup that occurs on or after July 1, 2024, the
4 Workgroup shall vote to adopt a code of conduct providing for the acceptable conduct of
5 Workgroup members.
6 (h) The Workgroup shall study and make recommendations regarding:
7 (1) the costs and availability of both publicly and privately provided
8 pretrial home detention monitoring systems;
9 (2) THE POLICIES AND PRACTICES THAT APPLY WHEN A PERSON
10 VIOLATES A CONDITION OF HOME DETENTION MONITORING SUCH AS ABSCONDING
11 FROM MONITORING; AND
12 (3) THE RESPONSES OF THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC SAFETY AND
13 CORRECTIONAL SERVICES AND HOME DETENTION MONITORING AGENCIES WHEN A
14 PERSON VIOLATES A CONDITION OF HOME DETENTION MONITORING.
15 (I) ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 1 EACH YEAR, THE DEPARTMENT OF
16 PUBLIC SAFETY AND CORRECTIONAL SERVICES SHALL COLLECT AND REPORT TO
17 THE WORKGROUP THE FOLLOWING DATA FOR THE PRIOR FISCAL YEAR:
18 (1) THE NUMBER OF PEOPLE PLACED ON HOME DETENTION
19 MONITORING, DISAGGREGATED BY RACE, GENDER, JURISDICTION, AND COMPANY
20 OR AGENCY PROVIDING THE HOME DETENTION MONITORING SERVICE;
21 (2) THE NUMBER OF TIMES A PERSON ON HOME DETENTION
22 MONITORING VIOLATED A CONDITION OF HOME DETENTION MONITORING,
23 DISAGGREGATED BY RACE, GENDER, JURISDICTION, NATURE OF THE VIOLATION,
24 AND COMPANY OR AGENCY PROVIDING THE HOME DETENTION MONITORING
25 SERVICE;
26 (3) THE NUMBER OF TIMES THAT A VIOLATION OF A CONDITION OF
27 HOME DETENTION MONITORING WAS REPORTED TO LAW ENFORCEMENT; AND
28 (4) THE NUMBER OF TIMES THAT A VIOLATION OF A CONDITION OF
29 HOME DETENTION MONITORING WAS REPORTED TO A JUDGE.
30 [(i)] (J) On or before December 31 each year, the Workgroup shall submit a
31 report of its findings and recommendations to the General Assembly, in accordance with §
32 2–1257 of the State Government Article.

